## Build & Tooling (source of truth)

Mechanics (how to build/run/test) come from these files, not from prose:

- @package.json — scripts, dependencies, package manager
- @tsconfig.json — TypeScript config and path aliases
- @.env.example — required environment variables (copy to `.env`, never commit `.env`)
- Lockfile (`package-lock.json` / `pnpm-lock.yaml` / `yarn.lock`) — the package manager in use; do not switch managers
- Build/dev config (`vite.config.*` / `next.config.*`) — bundler, aliases, env handling

## How To Build / Run

1. Read `package.json` scripts and run only scripts that exist.
2. Use the package manager implied by the lockfile.
3. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill required keys before running.

